    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CalculateTotalAccountEnergyUnitUsage",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to compute the total energy unit usage for a specific account. Scalar functions return a single value, which in this case, represents the total energy usage calculated based on the input parameters provided."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
